New Sect plan?<br>
I trust your dumbass conclusion refers to Invictus Dom.<br>
I consistently posted on the private forums that ID was NOT to 'take or supplant' Sabbat.  ID was to be a guild capable of doing stuff so that its members did not feel the need to join a sect like Sabbat or Synergy but that could join either at their chosing.<br>
<br>
Both Synergy and Sabbat rules allowed for doing stuff as a guild, just that members of one sect could not be a member of another sect.<br>
<br>
This was the goal.  That some saw it as a way that they could still do events and LEAVE Sabbat or Synergy was their perogative.  The majority clearly saw it as: a means to bridge the hostility between Sabbat and Synergy; could do things as a guild without the need to be a member of a sect; could support a sect as well (obviously for those who play a lot, a sect doesnt do enough, nor does a guild... but together should fill their time with meaningful play.)<br>
<br>
Many people from many guilds had informally agreed with the plan, and it was rolled out.  Sabbat falling apart led to ID falling apart.  This, above everything else, should point to the fact that the ideal of ID would be guild AND sect, not one at the expense of the other.<br>
<br>
When Sabbat was falling apart, I consistantly pushed for change, any change, that may pull it back together while striving to make sure people weren't made into scapegoats, such as Adell.<br>
<br>
Doing so may have made me unpopular on both sides (those for the Lugoj push and those for the status quo), but at least I have a clean conscience knowing I tried to make it work in a constructive manner.<br>
<br>
So next time you decide to make half-assed accusations, do try to get your facts straight, at least in regards with whom you direct those accusations.<br>
<br>
Rile / Fyrestaff<br>
